Class StandardLabeler<T extends Label>

  • edu.umn.nlpengine.StandardLabeler<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Labeler<T>

    public class StandardLabeler<T extends Label>
implements Labeler<T>

    A standard implementation of interface Labeler which handles the creation of interface LabelIndex instances.

    • Method Detail

      • getIndex

        public LabelIndex<T> getIndex()

        Upon first access creates the label index by turning everything added to this labeler into a new interface LabelIndex. After this labels can no longer be added to the labeler.

        Returns:
        Either returns a new label index or the existing label index created.
